5ï¸âƒ£ NAT (Network Address Translation) -------
ğŸ”¹ What is NAT?
    â¡ï¸ NAT is a networking technique that allows multiple devices in a private network to access the internet using one public IP address.

ğŸ‘‰ It translates private IP addresses â†’ public IP address and vice-versa.

ğŸ”¹ Why NAT is needed?
   âºï¸ IPv4 addresses are limited
   âºï¸ Internal (private) IPs are not routable on the internet
   âºï¸ Adds a basic layer of security
   âºï¸ Saves cost (one public IP for many devices)

ğŸ”¹ How NAT works (simple flow)
        Laptop (192.168.1.10)
                â†“
        Router (NAT)
                â†“
        Public IP (103.xx.xx.xx)
                â†“
        Internet

When the response comes back, NAT maps it back to:
    103.xx.xx.xx â†’ 192.168.1.10
    â¡ï¸ Private IP + Port â†’ Public IP + Port

